subsection.leadIn:
For the purposes of determining whether adequate means of escape are provided in accordance with the Code of Practice referred to in subsection (1)(a), the population of a karaoke establishment is to be calculated as follows—
(a) customers —1 m2/customer, calculated on the total floor area of the lounge, dining area and rooms intended to be used by customers, except toilets;
—0.75 m2/customer, calculated on the total floor area of the dancing area and reception area;
(b) staff —one staff member for every 20 customers or 4.5 m2/staff member, calculated on the total floor area of the kitchen and food preparation area, whichever is the greater.
